		<pb n="1"/>
          <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Barbados</placeName> <date>14 March 1848</date></p>
          <p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">My Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Your several forms with the &#8220;Occidents&#8221;<lb/> I have received&#44; but truly from the state of<lb/> mind I have been in&#44; it was impossible to<lb/> have replied earlier&#8212;this serves merely<lb/> to inform you&#44; that having consulted<lb/> with my dear wife&#44; we have resolved<lb/> with the blessing of God to remove our<lb/> family to <placeName><hi rend="underline">yankee town</hi></placeName> in the month<lb/> of June or July&#44; when I will settle with<lb/> you for whatever amount I may be<lb/> inobligated&#8212;on my arrival if in health&#44;<lb/> I shall feel much pleasure in rendering<lb/> you every assistance in my power in<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> in the Reading lines&#8212;please<lb/> hand the enclosed to our mutual<lb/> friend <persName>Mr. Carvalho</persName>&#44; and accept<lb/> from <persName>Mr. Daniels</persName> and self&#44; our<lb/> best wishes for your health and<lb/> happiness&#44; and believe me.</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">My Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">your&#39;s faithfully</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Samuel E. Daniels</persName></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
          <p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
